      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De exercitio</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e112">Apud Dominum non gradus elegantior, sed vitae
              melioris actio comprobatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e127">Qui ecclesiasticis famulantur obsequiis,
              ecclesiastica, ut possibilitas exigit, debent adipisci subsidia.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e142">Justitiam, quam mente geritis, oportet coram
              hominibus luce operum demonstretis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e157">Cum opus crescit, praemii fiducia proficit; cum
              vero opus torpuerit, spes a remuneratione lassescit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e173">Iste in hac vita justorum labor est, ut
              semetipsos inveniant; invenientes flendo atque corrigendo ad meliora
              perducant.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e180">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e188">Sicut malis securitas praesens labor est, ita
              bonis praesens labor perpetuam securitatem parit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e195">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e203">Sancti viri minime exultant cum cognoscunt quae
              faciant, sed cum faciunt quae cognoverunt: et si intelligendo congaudent muneri
              largitoris, moerentes tamen considerant debitum operis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e210">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e218">Activa vita est panem esurienti tribuere, verbum
              sapientiae nescientem docere, errantem corrigere, ad humilitatis viam superbientem
              proximum revocare, infirmantis curam gerere, et commissi nobis qualiter subsistere
              valeant, dispensare.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e223">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e233" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e225">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e233">Considerandum nobis est opus nostrum quale sit,
              quae cogitatio in opere, quae intentio in cogitatione.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e238">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e248" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e240">Gregorius, <title>super Ezechielem</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e248">Quid jam de Scriptura sacra didiceris, et
              quantum proximum tacitus ames, in latitudine boni operis ostendes.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e254">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e264" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e256">Gregorius, in <title>Dialogis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e264">Opus ex dono est, non donum ex opere. Omne
              quippe opus dona praeveniunt, quamvis ex subsequenti opere ipsa etiam dona
              succrescunt.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e269">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e279" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e271">Isidorus, in <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e279">Praecave otium; non diligas otium; non ducas
              vitam in otio: fatiga corpus laboribus; exerce operis cujuslibet studium.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e284">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e294" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e286">Isidorus, in <title>Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e294">Gravius libido urit, quem otiosum invenerit.
              Cedit autem libido rebus, cedit operi, cedit industriae et labori.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e299">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e309" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e301">Isidorus, <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e309">Nihil juvat, quod inter bonum et malum sensu
              prudentiore discernimus, nisi opere aut male cogitata caveamus, aut bona inchoata
              faciamus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e314">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e324" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e316">Isidorus, <title>de Summo Bono</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e324">Dei servum sine intermissione legere, orare, et
              operari oportet, ne forte mentem otio deditam spiritus fornicationis surripiat. Cedit
              enim labori voluptas; animum autem vacantem cito praeoccupat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e329">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e339" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e331">Joannes Chrysostomus, <title>super Matthaeum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e339">Qui habent spiritum Dei, non sunt contenti
              sedere otiosi; sed ipse spiritus, qui est in eis, urget eos aliquod bonum
              apprehendere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e345">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e355" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e347">Joannes Chrysostomus, <title>de Compunctione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e355">Merces major tibi augetur, quando non spe
              mercedis operaris, sed studio placendi.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e360">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e370" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e362">Augustinus, in <title>Sermone</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e370">Noli esse piger in opere, cujus mercedem
              desideras. Si quem et tu ipse mercenarium conduxisses, non ante mercedem numerares,
              quam in opere exerceres.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e375">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e385" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e377">Augustinus, <title>de Baptismo parvulorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e385">Propter hoc de paradiso emissus Adam contra Eden
              habitavit, id est contra sedem deliciarum, ut significaret, quod in laboribus, qui
              sunt deliciis contrarii, erudienda est caro peccati.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e390">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e400" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e392">Augustinus, <title>de Opere monachorum</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e400">Nullo modo decet, ut in ea vita, ubi senatores
              fiunt laboriosi, ibi fiant opifices otiosi; et quo veniunt, relictis deliciis, qui
              fuerunt praediorum domini, ibi sint rustici delicati.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e405">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e412" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e407">Augustinus, in glossa super I Tim., v</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e412">Qui ad pedes fratrum inclinatur, in corde vel
              excitatur, vel, si jam inerat, confirmatur humilitatis affectus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e417">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e427" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e419">Bernardus, <title>de Consideratione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e427">Si labor terret, merces invitet: unusquisque
              enim secundum suum laborem mercedem accipiet.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e433">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e443" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e435">Bernardus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e443">Non ex foliis, non ex floribus, sed ex fructu
              arbor bona, malave cognoscitur: denique: <!--<i>-->A fructibus eorum cognoscetis
              eos<!--</i>-->: opera ergo, et non verba, discernunt inter filios Dei, et filios
              diffidentiae.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e452">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e462" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e454">Bernardus, <title>de Amore Dei</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e462">Quamvis adhuc non videat oculus, non cesset
              operari manus: ut qui proficere vult in magno, fidelis sit in minimo; et in eo, quod
              ex Conditoris largitate jam praerogatum habet, vis potestatis officium exhibeat bonae
              voluntatis.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-d1e467">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e477" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Rd1e469">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e37534-Qd1e477">Satis multum temporis sparsimus, incipiamus vasa
              in senectute colligere: in freto viximus, moriamur in portu.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
